CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1956, pg. A2, reads: "Arabic Riddle - The young Fieldses, Marshall and Marsha, translate the Arabic riddles, which are their names, for Grandmother Agatha Fields of 95 Lafferty St. The bilingual youngsters speak English and Arabic which is their household language in Baghdad, Iraq, where their father is, a state department employe [employee]. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Marshall Fields pointing, and Marsha Fields, standing in front of Fields home, 95 Lafferty Street, Beltzhoover
